==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subtilization
<hw>Sub`til*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>subtilization</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of making
subtile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld> <def>The operation of making so
volatile as to rise in steam or vapor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Refinement; subtlety; extreme attenuation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subtilize</ent>⟦br⟧
